{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["65-JUD-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "JUD"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Jude \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Letter from Jude \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Jude \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Jud \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["The Letter from Jude \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "JUD 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JUD 1:1"}, "Jude,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Judah"]}], "caller": "+"}, " a servant of Al Masih Isa, and brother of Yaqub, to those who are called, sanctified\nby Allah the Father, and kept for Al Masih Isa: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JUD 1:2"}, "Mercy to you and peace and love be multiplied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JUD 1:3"}, "Beloved, while I was very eager to write to you about our common salvation, I was constrained to write to you exhorting\nyou to contend earnestly for the faith which was once for all delivered to the saints.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JUD 1:4"}, "For there are certain men who crept in secretly, even those who were long ago written about for this condemnation: ungodly\nmen, turning the grace of our Allah into indecency, and denying our only Master, Allah, and Lord, Al Masih Isa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JUD 1:5"}, "Now I desire to remind you, though you already know this, that the Lord, having saved a people out of the land of Egypt,\nafterward destroyed those who didn\u2019t believe. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JUD 1:6"}, "Angels who didn\u2019t keep their first domain, but deserted their own dwelling place, he has kept in everlasting bonds under\ndarkness for the judgement of the great day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JUD 1:7"}, "Even as Sodom and Gomorrah and the cities around them, having in the same way as these given themselves over to sexual\nimmorality and gone after strange flesh, are shown as an example, suffering the punishment of eternal fire.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JUD 1:8"}, "Yet in the same way, these also in their dreaming defile the flesh, despise authority, and slander celestial beings.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JUD 1:9"}, "But Michael, the archangel, when contending with the Iblis and arguing about the body of Musa, dared not bring against him\nan abusive condemnation, but said, \u201cMay the Lord rebuke you!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JUD 1:10"}, "But these speak evil of whatever things they don\u2019t know. They are destroyed in these things that they understand\nnaturally, like the creatures without reason. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JUD 1:11"}, "Woe to them! For they went in the way of Qabil, and ran riotously in the error of Balaam for hire, and perished in\nKorah\u2019s rebellion. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JUD 1:12"}, "These are hidden rocky reefs in your love feasts when they feast with you, shepherds who without fear feed themselves;\nclouds without water, carried along by winds; autumn trees without fruit, twice dead, plucked up by the roots;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JUD 1:13"}, "wild waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, for whom the blackness of darkness has been reserved\nforever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JUD 1:14"}, "About these also Enoch, the seventh from Adam, prophesied, saying,\n\u201cBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u1f30\u03b4\u03bf\u1f7a\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " the Lord came with ten thousands of his holy ones,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JUD 1:15"}, "to execute judgement on all, and to convict all the ungodly of all their works of ungodliness which they have done in an\nungodly way, and of all the hard things which ungodly sinners have spoken against him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JUD 1:16"}, "These are murmurers and complainers, walking after their lusts\u2014and their mouth speaks proud things\u2014showing respect of\npersons to gain advantage. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JUD 1:17"}, "But you, beloved, remember the words which have been spoken before by the apostles of our Lord Al Masih Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JUD 1:18"}, "They said to you, \u201cIn the last time there will be mockers, walking after their own ungodly lusts.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JUD 1:19"}, "These are those who cause divisions and are sensual, not having the Spirit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JUD 1:20"}, "But you, beloved, keep building up yourselves on your most holy faith, praying in the Holy Spirit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JUD 1:21"}, "Keep yourselves in Allah\u2019s love, looking for the mercy of our Lord Al Masih Isa to eternal life.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JUD 1:22"}, "On some have compassion, making a distinction, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JUD 1:23"}, "and some save, snatching them out of the fire with fear, hating even the clothing stained by the flesh.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JUD 1:24"}, "Now to him who is able to keep them", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR and NU read\n\u201cyou\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " from stumbling, and to present you faultless before the presence of his glory in great joy,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JUD 1:25"}, "to Allah our Saviour, who alone is wise, be glory and majesty, dominion and power, both now and forever. Amen.\n"]}]}